{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:46:05.147989+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 79ab8c039c4c3d3a54677f692f847917ad9dc553)", "id": "lc_04215336-d56c-44d4-a089-11aa1560c224"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />\n    <slot />\n    <DefaultFooter />\n  </div>\n</template>\n\n<script setup>\nimport DefaultFooter from './DefaultFooter.vue'\nimport DefaultNav from './DefaultNav.vue'\n\ndefineOptions({\n  name: 'DefaultLayout',\n})\n</script>\n\n<style lang=\"scss\">\n/* Sticky footer */\nhtml {\n  position: relative;\n  min-height: 100%;\n}\nbody {\n  margin-bottom: 60px; /* Margin bottom equal to footer height */\n}\n.default-page-wrapper {\n  padding: 5em 0em 3em 0em;\n}\n.footer {\n  position: absolute;\n  bottom: 0;\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 60px; /* Footer height */\n  line-height: 60px; /* Vertically center the text */\n  background-color: $gray-100;\n  text-align: center;\n}\n</style>\n", "id": "lc_0cc62501-9439-490b-a48f-fc65ba3f1419"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c7092e0c-38db-4c81-8bcc-3af9e7e02811", "tool_call_id": "call_7bf4d6c895ff47f8b1b281fd", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:46:28.537542+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I'll explain how the app bootstraps routing and layout rendering, and how the About page is loaded.\n\n## Bootstrapping Flow\n\n### 1. Entry Point\nThe HTML file `index.html` contains a `<div id=\"app\"></div>` and loads `/src/main.js` as a module script, which initializes the Vue application.\n\n### 2. Main Entry (`src/main.js`)\nThe main.js file performs the following steps:\n- Creates the Vue app using `createApp(App)`\n- Registers the `Default` layout component globally as `LayoutDefault`\n- Installs Pinia for state management\n- Installs the router\n- Mounts the app to `#app`\n\n### 3. Router Configuration (`src/router/index.js`)\nThe router uses hash-based history (`createWebHashHistory()`) and defines two routes:\n- **Home** (`/`): Eagerly loaded with `meta: { layout: 'default' }`\n- **About** (`/about`): Lazy-loaded with code-splitting and `meta: { layout: 'default' }`\n\n### 4. Layout Rendering (`src/App.vue`)\nThe root App component implements a dynamic layout system:\n```vue\n<component :is=\"layout\">\n  <RouterView />\n</component>\n```\nIt computes the layout name from `this.$route.meta.layout` (defaulting to `'default'`), so it renders as `layout-default` which maps to the globally registered `LayoutDefault` component.\n\n### 5. Default Layout (`src/layouts/default/Default.vue`)\nThe layout wraps content in a structure with navigation and footer:\n```vue\n<div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n  <DefaultNav />\n  <slot />  <!-- Page content renders here -->\n  <DefaultFooter />\n</div>\n```\n\n## How the About Page Loads\n\nWhen navigating to `/about`:\n\n1. **Route Matching**: Vue Router matches the `/about` path\n2. **Lazy Loading**: The About component is dynamically imported via `() => import('../views/About.vue')`\n3. **Layout Selection**: App.vue reads `meta.layout: 'default'` from the route\n4. **Component Rendering**: The layout wraps the About view in its slot, displaying navigation and footer\n\nThe About page itself (`src/views/About.vue`) is simple:\n```vue\n<template>\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <h1>This is the about page</h1>\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\n**Key architectural feature**: The dynamic layout system allows different pages to use different layouts by changing the `meta.layout` property in route definitions, while keeping layout concerns separate from page content.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1212, "prompt_tokens": 14962, "total_tokens": 16174, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 662, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 14592, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0012679212, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002134812, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00105444}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962365-YFrAZodBxu2eklNNJ8E1", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a1-0edc-76e1-9a8d-05d704ecabe5-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 14962, "output_tokens": 1212, "total_tokens": 16174, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 14592}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 662}}}}]}}}
